when object is created, whatever the code inside def__init__ (self,) will execute. That is called as constructor

class Employee:
    def __init__(self, name):
        print("Constructor is running...")
        self.name = name

emp1 = Employee("Nandha")


*****************Best way to explain**********************
More accurately:

__init__() is the constructor method in Python.
When an object is created, Python automatically calls __init__().
All the code inside __init__() runs at that moment.